OL,3,CAnnemarie Jacir's Palestine 36 retells
OL,4,Ccountry's erased anti-colonial history
OL,6,FWhen the British took over the running
OL,7,Fof Palestine in 1917, following the
OL,8,FBalfour declaration, in which the UK
OL,9,Fgovernment announced its support for a
OL,10,Fhomeland for Jewish people in
OL,11,FPalestine, the Arab population found
OL,12,Fitself watching as Jewish people who'd
OL,13,Fescaped antisemitism in Europe built
OL,14,Fsettlements on the land.
OL,16,FPalestine 36 depicts scenes of British
OL,17,Fbrutality and how ordinary villagers
OL,18,Fjoined to try to expel the colonisers.
